main event: Mr. Frank J. Winger sighted a circular unidentified flying object in Fairfield, Ohio on the evening of October 6, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as brightly lighted and silent, hovering at approximately 1,000 feet,The sighting was reported to the Fairfield Police Department and then to Project Blue Book,An investigation was conducted by Lt. G. C. Moore but no physical evidence was found,Mr. John Smith also reported seeing a pulsating orange light in the eastern sky on the same evening,The object reported by Winger suddenly accelerated and disappeared from sight.
witness description: Mr. Frank J. Winger and Mr. John Smith, residents of Fairfield, Ohio
